name: formats-suite
description: Derived from original keyed JSON inputs; adds concise per-format usage preambles for evaluating keyless JSON+CDDL retrieval behavior.
system: You answer questions using only the provided data. If the answer is not in the data, reply exactly: NOT_FOUND
template:
DATA ({{format}}):

{{format_preamble_block}}{{context}}

QUESTION:
{{question}}

INSTRUCTIONS:
- Use only the data above.
- Answer with only the final answer.
- Do not add punctuation or extra words.
- If the answer is not present, answer NOT_FOUND.

json_cddl.schema:
; Keyless employees dataset schema (CDDL)
employee = [
  id: uint,
  name: tstr,
  email: tstr,
  department: tstr,
  salary: uint,
  yearsExperience: uint,
  active: bool,
]

employees-dataset = [* employee]

questions.question: What is the email of the employee with id 42?
Which department does the employee named "Laura Schmitt" work in?
What is the salary of the employee with id 7?
Is the employee with id 88 active? Answer true or false.
How many employees are in the Engineering department?
What is the average salary of employees in Sales, rounded to the nearest integer?
How many employees have salary greater than 120000 and are active?
How many employees have more than 15 yearsExperience and are in Finance?

json_cddl.schema:
; Keyless orders dataset schema (CDDL)
customer = [
  id: uint,
  name: tstr,
  email: tstr,
  phone: tstr,
]

item = [
  sku: tstr,
  name: tstr,
  quantity: uint,
  price: float,
]

order = [
  orderId: tstr,
  customer: customer,
  items: [* item],
  subtotal: float,
  tax: float,
  total: float,
  status: tstr,
  orderDate: tstr,
]

orders-dataset = [* order]

questions.question: What is the status of order ORD-0025?
What is the total amount of order ORD-0010? Answer as a number.
What is the customer name for order ORD-0033?
How many line items are in order ORD-0040?
How many orders have status "shipped"?
What is the sum of total across all orders, rounded to 2 decimals? Answer as a number.
How many orders have total greater than 400 and status "delivered"?
How many orders contain an item with name "Webcam"?

json_cddl.schema:
; Keyless analytics dataset schema (CDDL)
metric = [
  date: tstr,
  views: uint,
  clicks: uint,
  conversions: uint,
  revenue: float,
  bounceRate: float,
]

metrics-dataset = [* metric]

questions.question: What are the views for 2025-01-15?
What is the revenue for 2025-02-10? Answer as a number.
What is the bounceRate for 2025-01-07? Answer as a number.
How many conversions were there on 2025-01-30?
How many days of data are in the metrics dataset?
What is the total number of views across all dates?
How many days had more than 6000 views?
How many days had more than 7000 views and more than 15 conversions?

json_cddl.schema:
; Keyless repositories dataset schema (CDDL)
repository = [
  id: uint,
  name: tstr,
  repo: tstr,
  description: tstr,
  stars: uint,
  watchers: uint,
  forks: uint,
  defaultBranch: tstr,
  createdAt: tstr,
  updatedAt: tstr,
  pushedAt: tstr,
]

repositories-dataset = [* repository]

questions.question: How many stars does repository "org7/project-42" have?
What is the defaultBranch of repository "org7/project-7"?
What is the createdAt date of repository "org1/project-1"?
How many forks does repository "org2/project-100" have?
How many repositories are in the dataset?
What is the total number of stars across all repositories?
How many repositories have more than 150000 stars?
How many repositories have defaultBranch "main" and more than 100000 stars?

json_cddl.schema:
; Keyless logs dataset schema (CDDL)
error = [
  message: tstr,
  code: tstr,
  retryable: bool,
]

log = [
  timestamp: tstr,
  level: tstr,
  endpoint: tstr,
  statusCode: uint,
  responseTime: uint,
  userId: uint,
  error: error / null,
]

logs-dataset = [* log]

questions.question: What is the level for the log entry with timestamp 2026-02-01T00:50:00Z?
What is the endpoint for the log entry with timestamp 2026-02-01T01:25:00Z?
What is the statusCode for the log entry with timestamp 2026-02-01T02:45:00Z?
Is error.retryable true for the log entry with timestamp 2026-02-01T00:05:00Z? Answer true or false.
How many log entries are in the logs dataset?
How many logs have level "error"?
How many logs have statusCode >= 500?
How many logs to endpoint "/api/orders" have statusCode >= 400?

json_cddl.schema:
; Keyless nested config schema (CDDL)
nested-config = [
  environment: tstr,
  version: tstr,
  database: any,
  features: any,
  authentication: any,
  permissions: any,
]

questions.question: What is the environment?
What is the database host?
What is the database pool max?
How many database replicas are configured?
What is the name of authentication provider #2 (second item in providers array)?
What is the first scope for the oauth2 authentication provider?
Is the darkMode feature enabled? Answer true or false.
How many permissions does the admin role have?

formatPreambles.json_cddl: Keyless JSON + CDDL indexing: arrays only (no object keys). Field meaning is fixed by array position from the CDDL schema. Relationships and complex values may use indexes, tags, enums, or bitmasks.
formatPreambles.toon: TOON format: read fixed field order in rows/blocks; parse values by position and labels shown in the rendered structure.
